title: A Cousin's Conspiracy
creator: Horatio Alger, Jr.
description: LibriVox recording of A Cousin's Conspiracy, by Horatio Alger, Jr. Read by Abigail Rasmussen. Ernest Ray is a young boy who sets out to reclaim the inheritance that was unjustly with held from his father and given to a cousin. (Introduction by Abigail Rasmussen) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; young adult; children; horatio alger; cousin's conspiracy
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: Very charming and interesting and attention-maintaining book in the quaint old fashioned style that I like, rather delightfully read by Abigail Rasmussen, who sounds remarkably similar to Alys Attewater who read Alger's most excellent *Ragged Dick* book.
reviews.reviewtitle: Excelent old fashioned Horatio Alger book with a very fine reader

reviews.reviewbody: Just finished listening to Cousin's Conspiracy, by Horatio Alger.  The reader does a very nice job.  This book strays from Alger's typical poor city boy makes good theme, and takes the orphaned teen out west for some great adventures with his friend, the "Quaker Detective".  As in all Alger books, good wins out in the end.  I think you'll enjoy this book, if you're a fan of the genre.
